Chlorine Purification



The facility fills chlorine ton containers to various purity grades. Commercial grade liquid chlorine is received in ton containers. Once the containers arrive at the facility they are offloaded and placed in the designated storage area until needed for purification. The ton container is hooked up to the process.  Chlorine is drawn from the source ton container and purified to the required purity grade through the removal of contaminants.  The purified chlorine is transferred to an empty receiving ton container. When the receiving tons are filled, they are carted back to the storage area.   When the purified chlorine ton containers are ordered, they are transferred to Building 200 for pickup.



Cylinder Storage



The facility is regulated for the storage of chemical cylinders listed above.  Some cylinders are filled onsite and then carted to the designated storage area.  Other cylinders are delivered to the facility by either a vendor or other Matheson Tri-Gas, Inc. sites.  The cylinders are stored onsite until distribution to customers or other Matheson sites.



ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS



Matheson Tri-Gas, Inc. has developed an accidental release prevention program for compliance with OSHA's PSM and EPA's RMP regulations.  The program includes but is not limited to the following elements:

?    Safety information regarding the chemical hazards, and operating and technical specifications for the process equipment;

?    Written procedures for operating and maintaining the processes;

